, in a now deleted comment.\", \"from\": 15339, \"to\": 15409, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And there is this pesky fact:  Apollo is the symbol of reason - the god of thought, deliberation, light.\", \"from\": 15411, \"to\": 15515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15442, \"end\": 15448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\", \"score\": 0.999999912292996, \"rank\": 8.770573322060346e-08, \"text\": \"Apollo\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(And that is how he is depicted in the Bijlert painting.)\", \"from\": 15516, \"to\": 15573, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In classical sculpture, he is presented as an idealized, human nude - strong, upright, confident.\", \"from\": 15574, \"to\": 15671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Those [expletives deleted] present Apollo as an ugly, obese, perverted brute cheering a drunken orgy.\", \"from\": 15673, \"to\": 15774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15708, \"end\": 15714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\", \"score\": 0.9968948855859474, \"rank\": 0.0030122999835117637, \"text\": \"Apollo\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So what we have from this culture of nihilism is a double mockery: Of Christianity and of Apollo.\", \"from\": 15776, \"to\": 15873, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15846, \"end\": 15858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.998421512507904, \"rank\": 0.0009466820202280624, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 15866, \"end\": 15872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\", \"score\": 0.9968948855859474, \"rank\": 0.0030122999835117637, \"text\": 