 []}, {\"sentence\": \"Marx wrote that in order for communist totalitarian utopia to replace existing Western cultures with elected governments (like France, England and Belgium where he lived), the existing pillars of their civil societies had to be destroyed.\", \"from\": 16147, \"to\": 16385, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16147, \"end\": 16151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Marx\", \"score\": 0.9990724846553989, \"rank\": 0.0009283673930564575, \"text\": \"Marx\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Marx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Marx\"}, {\"begin\": 16274, \"end\": 16280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7867789380179238, \"rank\": 0.23538091157395133, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 16282, \"end\": 16289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"score\": 0.5543173894036603, \"rank\": 0.7213749118467586, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 16294, \"end\": 16301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9796969645309179, \"rank\": 0.020465504750520766, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Belief in those values had to be destroyed by whatever means necessary - because communism's success required that its subjects only have loyalty to and value the state.\", \"from\": 16387, \"to\": 16556, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, the values of a nuclear family?\", \"from\": 16558, \"to\": 16593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Destroy them.\", \"from\": 16595, \"to\": 16608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Heterosexual marriages and children raised with heterosexual values?\", \"from\": 16610, \"to\": 16678, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Destroy that.\", \"from\": 16680, \"to\": 16693, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Religious principles to attempt to live your life doing your best to adhere to?\", \"from\": 16695, \"to\": 16774, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Destroy that - replace that with atheism and it's central tenant of hating religion; the only worship will be worship of The Communist State.\", \"from\": 16776, \"to\": 16917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16901, \"end\": 16916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communist_state\", \"score\": 0.994465146251687, \"rank\": 0.005555957280329152, \"text\": \"Communist State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communist_state\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communist_state\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Communism's Long March (Marx and Engels NEVER called their political screed \\\"Marxism\\\") is not just political Marxism or economic Marxism.\", \"from\": 16919, \"to\": 17056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16919, \"end\": 16928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communism\", \"score\": 0.9994606749604059, \"rank\": 0.0005358039597358755, \"text\": \"Communism\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communism\"}, {\"begin\": 16931, \"end\": 16941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Long_March\", \"score\": 0.9999999949330913, \"rank\": 5.064967015836742e-09, \"text\": \"Long March\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Long_March\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Long_March\"}, {\"begin\": 16943, \"end\": 16947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Marx\", \"score\": 0.9982947425310783, \"rank\": 0.0017081678055302061, \"text\": \"Marx\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"]