se dismissed twice but failed.\", \"from\": 30993, \"to\": 31073, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 30997, \"end\": 31017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\", \"score\": 0.9938309212369738, \"rank\": 0.006207372533105557, \"text\": \"Biden administration\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On June 28, the U.S. District Court for the Northern District of Texas ruled that the lawsuit can proceed, and that there is evidence the Biden administration continued awarding taxpayer cash to UNRWA even after Congress blocked funding to that group due to its support for Hamas's military infrastructure.\", \"from\": 31074, \"to\": 31380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 31139, \"end\": 31144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas\", \"score\": 0.9999992708814418, \"rank\": 6.943366025347666e-07, \"text\": \"Texas\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas\"}, {\"begin\": 31212, \"end\": 31232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\", \"score\": 0.688817904721823, \"rank\": 0.4517449879512682, \"text\": \"Biden administration\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\"}, {\"begin\": 31269, \"end\": 31274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNRWA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UNRWA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNRWA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNRWA\"}, {\"begin\": 31286, \"end\": 31294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\", \"score\": 0.9999980914531102, \"rank\": 1.251197073493647e-06, \"text\": \"Congress\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\"}, {\"begin\": 31348, \"end\": 31353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamas\", \"score\": 0.9999999725238243, \"rank\": 2.7476149860104087e-08, \"text\": \"Hamas\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"https://www.gatestoneinstitute.org/20811/biden-administration-donates-to-hamas  If, under French law, it constitutes criminal \\\"hate speech\\\" to complain about what's perceived as an insult to one's religion, would not it also be criminal \\\"hate speech\\\" to ridicule one's religion, as the \\\"Dionysus Last Supper\\\" appeared to do?\", \"from\": 31382, \"to\": 31706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 31472, \"end\": 31482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9999491566543994, \"rank\": 5.0664144794222546e-05, \"text\": \"French law\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And in a country where a perceived insult to Mohammed was handled by murdering the publisher, would not civil discussion of the issue be a less hateful response?\", \"from\": 31708, \"to\": 31869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Seems there has been many quotes from participants in this shambolic event confirming that it was a parody of the last supper and now they only want tolerance.\", \"from\": 31871, \"to\": 32030, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Their hypocrisy is without bounds and they should receive as much tolerance as they showed.\", \"from\": 32031, \"to\": 32122, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If anything, in present day France, they should have criminal charges lodged against them for the mocking and degrading of a religion.\", \"from\": 32123, \"to\": 32257, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 32151, \"end\": 32157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.8237582588439206, \"rank\": 0.1920406411157502, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If Mr. LePen can be charged for calling the Romani smelly, or a teenager charged for calling Islam a \\\"religion of hate\\\" or Ms Bardot can be charged, then surely, under French law, these so-called performers should be charged for mocking and thereby slandering and degrading a religion.Now if this event  were in the United States I would say nothing except turn off the TV, and not watch another minute of Olympic coverage (which I am doing anyway) but I am looking at precedent under French Law and even under the Napoleonic Code it should remain consistent, should it not.As an alternative I would suggest repeating the event and let every French Citizen or Olympic Games ticket holder come to the repeat event and being allowed to throw pies, of any flavor, at the participants in the event, from a distance of about 5 feet.\", \"from\": 32258, \"to\": 33085, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 32265, \"end\": 32270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LEPEN_(political_party)\", \"score\": 0.8020135056823037, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LePen\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LEPEN_(political_party)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LEPEN_(political_party)\"}, {\"begin\": 32302, \"end\": 32308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romani_people\", \"score\": 0.9999561204433933, \"rank\": 2.7697679785121347e-05, \"text\": \"Romani\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romani_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romani_people\"}, {\"begin\": 32384, \"end\": 32390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brigitte_Bardot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.332839089514984e-15, \"text\": \"Bardot\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brigitte_Bardot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brigitte_Bardot\"}, {\"begin\": 32426, \"end\": 32436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9797065403054543, \"rank\": 0.019982456270056265, \"text\": \"French law\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 32574, \"end\": 32587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999753854932243, \"rank\": 2.4056632171000702e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 32743, \"end\": 32753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Law\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 32900, \"end\": 32906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9940509033308964, \"rank\": 0.00472995485926349, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That would be about enough tolerance but alas such a waste of good French pastries.On the other hand we could just throw fresh pear tarts at them, sort of like a TARTS for TARTS event.\", \"from\": 33086, \"to\": 33270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33153, \"end\": 33159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9940509033308964, \"rank\": 0.00472995485926349, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But I must admit seeing fresh pear tarts in the air flying towards destruction would bring tears to my eyes.\", \"from\": 33271, \"to\": 33379, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"GEB,The pie throwing scene in Blazing Saddles just popped into my mind.\", \"from\": 33381, \"to\": 33452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33381, \"end\": 33384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gujarat_Urja_Vikas_Nigam\", \"score\": 0.999999931308596, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"GEB\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gujarat_Urja_Vikas_Nigam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gujarat_Urja_Vikas_Nigam\"}, {\"begin\": 33411, \"end\": 33426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blazing_Saddles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Blazing Saddles\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blazing_Saddles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blazing_Saddles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"GEB, Great comment!\", \"from\": 33454, \"to\": 33473, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33454, \"end\": 33457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gujarat_Urja_Vikas_Nigam\", \"score\": 0.999999931308596, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"GEB\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gujarat_Urja_Vikas_Nigam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gujarat_Urja_Vikas_Nigam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I admit seeingFresh pear tarts flying towardsDestruction brings tears  Statement by producer, Thomas Jolly: \\\"We wanted to include everyone, as simple as that.\", \"from\": 33475, \"to\": 33633, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In France, we have freedom of creation, artistic freedom.\", \"from\": 33634, \"to\": 33691, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33637, \"end\": 33643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.5576272144069716, \"rank\": 0.7389946608609709, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are lucky in France to live in a free country.\", \"from\": 33692, \"to\": 33741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33708, \"end\": 33714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.5576272144069716, \"rank\": 0.7389946608609709, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not have any specific messages that I wanted to deliver.\", \"from\": 33742, \"to\": 33804, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In France, we are a republic, we have the right to love whom we want, we have the right not to be worshippers, we have a lot of rights in France, and this is what I wanted to convey.\\\"\", \"from\": 33805, \"to\": 33988, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33808, \"end\": 33814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.5576272144069716, \"rank\": 0.7389946608609709, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 33943, \"end\": 33949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.5576272144069716, \"rank\": 0.7389946608609709, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly wanted to include everyone, because Christianity obviously does not?\", \"from\": 33990, \"to\": 34064, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 34032, \"end\": 34044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9980910227540924, \"rank\": 0.0012741920540540626, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The intent, as Turley states, is to be provocative.\", \"from\": 34065, \"to\": 34116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Note too that children were included in Jolly's diverse, sexual statement smorgasbord.\", \"from\": 34117, \"to\": 34203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Add that I am actually appalled at what appears to be rapidly diminishing rights in Western European countries.\", \"from\": 34205, \"to\": 34316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 34289, \"end\": 34296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.9944674667934695, \"rank\": 0.005453324862725407, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Trump's recent gag order?\", \"from\": 34317, \"to\": 34342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 34317, \"end\": 34322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999956683391841, \"rank\": 3.5462061318005634e-06, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's standard-fare in England, defendants are not permitted to discuss their cases in public, to offer explanation to family and friends, to defend themselves in the public sphere.\", \"from\": 34343, \"to\": 34525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 34367, \"end\": 34374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"score\": 0.8993948302562, \"rank\": 0.10761027975255671, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"People ARE arrested for speech.\", \"from\": 34526, \"to\": 34557, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For those who followed the Hillsborough Stadium disaster, police officers were actually charged with murder, crimes they very obviously did not commit.\", \"from\": 34558, \"to\": 34709, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Charged, it would seem, for political purpose, to appease a public determined to hold someone, anyone, accountable.\", \"from\": 34710, \"to\": 34825, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has always made me laugh too to hear the English discuss constitutional rights - the word itself actually appears here as early as 1620 in the Mayflower Compact - but to this day the English have no constitution and they have no rights.\", \"from\": 34826, \"to\": 35065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 34870, \"end\": 34877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\", \"score\": 0.8343994580823983, \"rank\": 0.14278092786705673, \"text\": \"English\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\"}, {\"begin\": 34972, \"end\": 34989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mayflower_Compact\", \"score\": 0.9999955167980258, \"rank\": 4.483222047108248e-06, \"text\": \"Mayflower Compact\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mayflower_Compact\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mayflower_Compact\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brought to light again during the Canadian Covid convoy protests which saw the accounts of hundreds of protesters frozen, and the denial of bail, etc.\", \"from\": 35066, \"to\": 35216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 35100, \"end\": 35108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.5327634570565637, \"rank\": 0.838482505297896, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Canada, as I understand it, is still a British constitutional monarchy, today under Charles III, but executive power resides with the Crown and the people, so \\\"constituted,\\\" have no rights.\", \"from\": 35217, \"to\": 35406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 35217, \"end\": 35223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.7824922778811231, \"rank\": 0.277942663825363, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 35256, \"end\": 35263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9648919881972178, \"rank\": 0.02244118878539627, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 35301, \"end\": 35312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_III_of_Spain\", \"score\": 0.9979209102094292, \"rank\": 0.0017015471751530332, \"text\": \"Charles III\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_III_of_Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_III_of_Spain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly-> we just wanted to include everyone?\", \"from\": 35408, \"to\": 35451, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone EXCEPT about a billion Christians.\", \"from\": 35452, \"to\": 35495, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 35484, \"end\": 35494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"score\": 0.7878413527492902, \"rank\": 0.23592795008557851, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Actually they were deceptively invited to the Olympic party to be abused of course.\", \"from\": 35496, \"to\": 35579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sadism is fun.\", \"from\": 35580, \"to\": 35594, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's acceptable.\", \"from\": 35595, \"to\": 35613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps newsguard has a a censorship category for Christians?\", \"from\": 35615, \"to\": 35676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 35665, \"end\": 35675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.6146622601046808, \"rank\": 0.5081283775789419, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If so many people think it is clearly The Last Passover Supper of Christ then what a miserable failure in communication!\", \"from\": 35677, \"to\": 35797, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Butch with a nimbus identifies it so stop making shit up.\", \"from\": 35799, \"to\": 35856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wrong venue , Mr. Jolly.\", \"from\": 35858, \"to\": 35882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Know your audience.\", \"from\": 35883, \"to\": 35902, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's Mardi Gras for everyone.\", \"from\": 35903, \"to\": 35932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 35908, \"end\": 35918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mardi_Gras\", \"score\": 0.9999993994702647, \"rank\": 3.844230529280762e-07, \"text\": \"Mardi Gras\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mardi_Gras\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mardi_Gras\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For newsguard censor purposes the rating is immoral content.\", \"from\": 35933, \"to\": 35993, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not bother to watch unless you are masochistic and really enjoy some fugly shit.\", \"from\": 35995, \"to\": 36078, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Comments are closed.\", \"from\": 36080, \"to\": 36100, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Enter your email address to subscribe to this blog and receive notifications of new